Lucca serves thin, crispy, delicious pies full of fresh ingredients and the perfect balance of crust:sauce:cheese.  However, during my most recent couple of visits the service has been underwhelming at best. They are not succeeding in making me feel like my business is appreciated at all. On top of that, it has been very frustrating to see servers engaged in chit chat while ignoring the guests. I am 100% for employees to enjoy work, make friends, and develop good relationships with each other - but not at the expense of making the customer feel more like a burden than a welcome guest.  The pizza can't be beat if you're a fan of thin, crispy pies; so I will continue to visit! I hope that service improves so I can revert to the 5 star review that the flavor and quality of the food truly deserves!

Changed the Dago steak sandwich recipe to a frickin’ hamburger that was very dry and had the flavor of a White Castle burger. It was very small and not worth the $10 they charge for it. I’d gladly pay the $10 for the original recipe the way it was. I was there last October and the recipe was perfect and nowhere near like the mess I had today. I’ve been coming to this restaurant for over 40 years and today was the first time I’ve ever been disappointed by the food. I gave 3 stars because the service is always good and the atmosphere hasn’t changed which gives me very special memories of my dad bringing me in to the Lucca for their awesome sandwiches. PLEASE bring the original recipes back!!! PLEASE!!!

We were beyond disappointed when we followed an amazing aroma to The Lucca Grill where we were turned away as they were only accommodating reservations at that time. We made sure to make reservations for our next trip to Bloomington and we were NOT disappointed!! The artichoke dip was unique and addicting!! The classic thin crust stone oven baked pizza was perfectly topped and evenly cooked to perfection. And the Straccali(?) Pasta dish was... wow. Not to mention, Candi, our server was outstanding!! We had everything we needed when we needed it and she even gave us parking tips for our show after dinner! To top it off the owner came and introduced himself, offered his business card and thanked us for our business. What an outstanding experience. We will be back!

Very good server.  Attentive, knowledgeable, intuitive.  Came with a group.  Enjoyed a few pizzas, but wished we'd asked for extra cheese on them.  Loved the thin crust.  Felt that the appetizers were a hair overpriced.  Onion rings we're good.  Fries were skimpy for the price and size.  Chicken livers were dry, dry, dry...which alway makes me sad.  The largest issue was getting in.  We tried the week before and were told it would be an hour wait and we'd have to eat upstairs if we didn't have a reservation.  That info would be good to have online.  We ended up elsewhere that night.  But when we called in a reservation for this night I was put on hold while someone checked the schedule...then told it depended on be when and how many (which could have been shared before they put me on hold) and after the reservation was cleared was told we could only do it if the table was cleared in 90 minutes for a later reservation.  Part of me understands the desire for clarity...and the other part wonders if they really want customers.  At least wonders if they want new ones.  Between the two experiences, it was off-putting.  We'll visit again, but I doubt it will be often.
